---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | AutomatorLabs"
  description="Read how AutomatorLabs handles calculator inputs, analytics data, local preferences, and messages submitted through contact links."
>
  <main id="main-content">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li aria-current="page">Privacy</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        This policy explains the basic information practices of AutomatorLabs.
        It was last updated on June 15, 2026.
      </p>
    </header>

    <article class="policy">
      <section>
        <h2>What AutomatorLabs provides</h2>
        <p>
          AutomatorLabs provides free financial calculators and educational
          guides. You do not need to create an account or sign in to use the
          site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Calculator inputs</h2>
        <p>
          Calculator inputs may be processed in your browser to generate
          results. AutomatorLabs does not intentionally ask for or collect
          sensitive personal data through calculator forms. You should not
          enter account numbers, passwords, government identifiers, or other
          confidential information.
        </p>
        <p>
          After a successful calculation, input values may appear in the page
          URL so the calculation can be shared. Anyone who receives that URL
          may be able to read those values, and URLs can be stored in browser
          history or server logs. Use general planning figures rather than
          sensitive information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Google Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          AutomatorLabs uses Google Analytics to understand general site usage,
          such as page visits and calculator activity. Google may process
          information including device and browser details, approximate
          location, referring pages, and interactions with the site according
          to Google's own privacy practices.
        </p>
        <p>
          Calculator usage events identify which calculator was used. They are
          not designed to include the financial values entered into calculator
          fields.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Local preferences</h2>
        <p>
          The site may use browser storage to remember preferences such as
          light or dark mode. This information stays associated with your
          browser unless you clear it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact and GitHub links</h2>
        <p>
          Contact links may take you to GitHub or another external service.
          Messages, bug reports, and suggestions you submit there are provided
          voluntarily and are handled under that service's privacy terms. Do
          not include sensitive personal or financial information in a public
          issue.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>External links and changes</h2>
        <p>
          AutomatorLabs may link to external websites that have their own
          privacy practices. This policy may be updated when site features or
          data practices change. The date above will be revised when material
          updates are made.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Questions</h2>
        <p>
          Questions or concerns about this policy can be shared through the
          <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  main {
    width: min(820px, calc(100% - 2rem));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .breadcrumbs {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--muted-text-color);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .breadcrumbs ol {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .breadcrumbs li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .breadcrumbs li + li::before {
    color: var(--muted-text-color);
    content: '›';
  }

  .breadcrumbs a,
  .policy a {
    color: var(--link-color);
  }

  .breadcrumbs a {
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumbs a:hover,
  .policy a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .breadcrumbs [aria-current='page'] {
    color: var(--text-color);
    font-weight: 650;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    color: var(--link-color);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 7vw, 4rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.045em;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .intro {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    color: var(--muted-text-color);
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .policy {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: var(--card-background);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 35px var(--shadow-color);
    padding: clamp(1.4rem, 5vw, 2.4rem);
  }

  .policy section + section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    margin-top: 1.8rem;
    padding-top: 1.8rem;
  }

  .policy h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .policy p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted-text-color);
    line-height: 1.78;
  }

  .policy p + p {
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    main {
      padding-top: 3rem;
    }
  }
</style>
